<br>
The rest are people who had their &quot;choice&quot; when they chose to have sex, and could have used a condom/pill/etc, and now don't want to take responsibility for that choice.<br>
<br>
As a woman who got pregnant at 16, I was in the position of everyone telling me to have an abortion because it would be &quot;better for the baby and me&quot;.  Well, if you ask my 17 year old daughter now, she'll tell you it sure as hell wouldn't have been better for her.  And yeah, I gave up a lot in my life to be able to have her - but she has been worth every minute of it.<br>
<br>
Dead is never better than alive.  Give the kid a chance, put it up for adoption if you don't want it.  And don't tell me it isn't a baby - legal precedents show you can be convicted of two murders if you kill a pregnant woman, so that gives an unborn child some legal status right there.  Let's do some simple logic here...<br>
<br>
Put a sperm in ideal conditions for 9 months - ya got a live or dead sperm.  BFD.  Same thing with an unfertilized egg.<br>
<br>
Put a fertilized egg, fetus, whatever the heck ya wanna call it, in ideal conditions for nine months, and you got a baby.  Personally, I don't wanna take the chance on exactly WHEN that &quot;became&quot; a baby.  Just have the kid and if you don't want it, give it to someone who does.  I personally know of 3 people in my office who'd love to adopt, and that's a drop in the bucket.  <br>
<br>
People who argue for abortion just don't make sense to me.  And as a professional, degreed woman (and yeah, amazingly, I got two master's degrees while a single parent!  My life wasnt ruined by being a pregnant teenager, OMG!) I am supposed to be one of the fanatic feminists who think abortions should be legal at all costs.  The problem is, the more I thought about it instead of just buying all the &quot;freedom to choose&quot; jargon that had always been fed to me, the less it made sense to me.<br>
<br>
Flame away, I haven't gotten flamed in a while on here, so I figured I might as well start something - but yeah, unlike some of my usual BS trying to start something, these are my actual opinions on the subject. <br>
